From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: NextOS-Elite-Edition <noreply@nextos>
Date: Mon, 27 Apr 2026 23:30:00 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] gsupplicant: prefer WPA-PSK over SAE for transition-mode APs

Upstream connman 2.0 sends key_mgmt="SAE WPA-PSK WPA-PSK-SHA256" for any
PSK-capable AP, which causes wpa_supplicant to attempt SAE first. On APs
running WPA2/WPA3 transition mode (Authentication suites: PSK SAE, MFP
optional), wpa connects with SAE momentarily but connman re-evaluates
and disconnects on key_mgmt mismatch — yielding "invalid-key" errors
even though credentials are correct.

Reorder so PSK is tried first, with SAE retained as fallback. This
preserves WPA3-only AP support while fixing transition-mode connectivity
on common consumer routers (TP-Link, Mercusys, ASUS, etc.).

Symptom without patch: WiFi connects briefly, gets IP, then drops with
"invalid-key" — only fixable per-network via /var/lib/connman/wifi.config
with explicit Security=psk.

diff --git a/gsupplicant/supplicant.c b/gsupplicant/supplicant.c
--- a/gsupplicant/supplicant.c
+++ b/gsupplicant/supplicant.c
@@ -4955,7 +4955,7 @@ static void add_network_security(DBusMessageIter *dict, GSupplicantSSID *ssid)
 		add_network_security_ciphers(dict, ssid);
 		break;
 	case G_SUPPLICANT_SECURITY_PSK:
-		key_mgmt = "SAE WPA-PSK WPA-PSK-SHA256";
+		key_mgmt = "WPA-PSK WPA-PSK-SHA256 SAE";
 		ieee80211w = G_SUPPLICANT_MFP_OPTIONAL;
 		add_network_ieee80211w(dict, ssid, ieee80211w);
 		add_network_security_psk(dict, ssid);
